to fix this thing.

247
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:58,753
Well...
[ Chuckle ]

248
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:01,155
how did you come
to be a nanny?

249
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:03,999
Well, um...

250
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:06,918
a few years ago
l was pregnant.

251
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:10,157
l lost the baby and my husband
within days of each other.

252
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:13,277
The miscarriage prevented me
from having more children.

253
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,231
lt was a very
difficult time.

254
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:19,035
A mutual friend set me up
with a family looking for a nanny.

255
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:23,472
lt turned out to be... a wonderful
experience for both of us.

256
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:25,710
l adore children.

257
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:29,310
l love being with them,
taking care of them.

258
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,635
For me it's...

259
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:35,838
the next best thing
to actually being a mother.

260
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:38,679
Well, l'm building
my own greenhouse.

261
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:42,031
And... although l'll just be
right in the backyard,

262
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:44,469
l'm anticipating
being very busy.

263
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,397
[ Crying ]

264
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,995
That's Joe.

265
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,991
Oh!
l'd love to meet him.

266
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:57,318
The nursery is across
from the master bedroom.

267
00:20:57,440 --> 00:21:01,115
[ Solomon ]
Claire? l need to ask you something.

268
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:03,913
l'll be right back.
Excuse me.

269
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:18,592
[ Crying, Cooing ]

270
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:40,116
[ Claire ]
Try to open the window from the inside.

271
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:42,839
lf you can't, wait
till Michael comes home.

272
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:45,269
Solomon, this is Peyton.
Peyton, Solomon.

273
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:48,836
- Nice to meet you, Solomon.
- Oh, hello.

274
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:50,279
[ Gasp ]

275
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:54,359
Oh, l'm sorry!
l'm sorry.

276
00:21:58,080 --> 00:22:02,039
- l'm sorry.
- That's all right. lt was an accident.

277
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:04,475
Anyone can have an accident.

278
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,591
Okay.

279
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:29,078
Ohh!
He's beautiful.

280
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,077
He's very hungry.

281
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:35,075
l've taken up
half your morning.

282
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,997
No problem,
l really enjoyed it.

283
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:40,396
l should be going. l'm gonna
leave a letter of reference.

284
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:43,472
l can show myself out.
You don't have to get up.

285
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:47,673
Peyton, would you like to
have dinner with us tonight?

286
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,631
l'd love for you
to meet the family.

287
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:51,318
l'd love to.

288
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,396
Say around 6:30?

289
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:56,278
l'll be here.

290
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:02,593
l'm in charge of
the salad dressing.

291
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:05,473
And now you're in charge of setting
the table, sweetheart.

292
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:07,875
Daddy's gonna be home
any minute.

293
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,992
lf you don't mind my asking,
what does your husband do?

294
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:12,911
Michael's a
genetic engineer.

295
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,673
He works for a research
outfit called Biotechnics.

296
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,552
Daddy is a
mad scientist!

297
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:19,756
[ Honking ]

298
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:21,319
lt's Daddy!

299
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:27,312
Here, let me help
with that.

300
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,192
Thanks.

301
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:32,556
Gimme a kiss.
Thank you very much.

302
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:34,631
- You helping Mom out, huh?
- Shh.

303
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:37,518
What are you
shushing me for?

304
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:41,388
[ Whispering ]
Oh, Joey's asleep. Thank you.

305
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:42,999
Shh.

306
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,076
- [ Michael ] Hi, beautiful.
- How are you?

307
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:55,232
- Peyton, this is my husband, Michael.
- Hi.

308
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:01,349
[ Michael ]
l gotta tell you guys,

309
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:04,955
- that was one of
the all-time great meals.
- lt was delicious.

310
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,640
l was in charge
of the salad dressing.

311
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:11,793
That's right. She did.
She made it all by herself.

312
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:18,669
When Mom finishes
the greenhouse,

313
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:21,439
- l'm in charge of the strawberries.
- Really?

314
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:25,712
- That sounds like a very important job.
- lt is.

315
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:33,953
[ Whispering ]
She seems terrific. What's the catch?

316
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:36,913
There is no catch.
l think she's great.

317
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:40,077
l don't think she'll be a nanny
forever, but we can get her
to commit for a year.

318
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:43,277
- [ Michael ] Let's grab her up.
- Yeah? Okay.

319
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:47,910
[ Gasp ]
Oh my God!

320
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,672
[ Crying ]

321
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:52,115
- What happened?
- He had this in his mouth.

322
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:55,471
- Mommy's earring.
- lt must have fallen out
when l was holding him.

323
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:57,079
He's okay.

324
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:00,272
l'm sorry
l frightened everybody.

325
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:03,153
- l'm glad you caught it.
- l'm glad you got there on time.

326
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:22,992
[ Doorbell ]

327
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,957
- Hi.
- Hi.

328
00:25:25,080 --> 00:25:29,392
- This is for you.
- Oh, thank you.
You didn't have to do that.

329
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:31,675
[ Chiming ]

330
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:34,360
Oh, that's
very pretty.

331
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:37,193
They say a wind chime
helps a baby sleep.

332
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,874
Why don't we get
you settled downstairs,

333
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:43,515
- then we'll hang it up
outside the nursery.
- Okay.

334
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:58,399
This is a little bit dark,
but your room gets more light.

335
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:02,836
This is...
the laundry room.

336
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:10,320
And this is your room.

337
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:15,316
- Ah... it's perfect.
- You like it?

338
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:24,471
[ Alarm ]

339
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:03,957
[ Chiming ]

340
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:27,236
[ Cooing ]

341
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:24,552
There we go.

342
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,994
Mom, look!
We did it.

343
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:57,993
Oh boy!
Let's see.

344
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:04,193
- Emma, you can certainly shovel!
- Thank you.

345
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,788
How pretty!

346
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:09,713
lt looks just like
your house.

347
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:12,439
Yeah, l know.
We put it out every year...

348
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,988
when the martins come back.

349
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:18,835
Who are the martins?

350
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:21,520
They're large swallows.

351
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:24,273
The same family comes back
every year to visit us.

352
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:26,709
Yeah!

353
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:29,559
l would come back too.

354
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:38,400
That is a beautiful
bracelet, Claire.

355
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:41,080
You like that?
l got that at an antique show.

356
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:44,590
- You can borrow it anytime.
- Well, thank you.

357
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:49,830
This must be
a special occasion.

358
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:53,708
l always feel sexy and glamorous
when l wear this dress.

359
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,916
lt's a present
from Michael.

360
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,195
Okay...

361
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:01,073
which shoes should l wear,
red or black?

362
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:05,073
- Are you wearing a jacket?
- Yeah. Well, no.

363
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:07,873
- Maybe not.
- Then l'd go with the black.

364
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:09,797
You think so?

365
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:15,635
[ Claire ]
Yeah, l guess you're right.

366
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:21,077
- [ Doorbell ]
- That's them. Now l'm really late.

367
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:24,112
- Where are you guys?
- Oh, we're running late.

368
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:27,357
-Where's Marlene? She want to come in?
-Nah, she's on the phone.

369
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:31,991
Oh damn.

370
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:35,351
- What is it?
- lt's just a stain.

371
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:38,153
lt's perfume oil.

372
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:40,310
l must have perfume oil
on my hands.

373
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:43,796
-Don't move. l'll go get some club soda.
-Thanks.

374
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,399
Marty, this is... Peyton.

375
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:57,876
- Hello, Peyton.
- Hello. Nice to meet you.

376
00:30:57,960 --> 00:31:00,474
- l need to get something for Claire.
- Okay.

377
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:03,114
[ Marty ]
Whew!

378
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:06,397
Maybe we should
go ahead and have kids.

379
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:13,914
l just want to inform everybody that
this place will not hold our table.

380
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,951
- Hello, Marlene.
- Hello.

381
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,351
What's with you?

382
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:21,835
What do you mean?
Nothing's with me.

383
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:28,869
Nothing my ass.

384
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,190
Hi, l don't
believe we've met.

385
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:35,757
-l'm Marlene Craven. You must be Peyton.
-Nice to meet you.

386
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:37,717
- Poison.
- Excuse me?

387
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:41,395
- The perfume. You're
wearing Claire's perfume.
- Oh.

388
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:44,751
Well, Claire
needs me upstairs.

389
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:53,796
You look great.

390
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:01,518
- You don't think that's funny?
- No.

391
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:08,630
There she is.

392
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:10,910
- Hi. Sorry.
- Hi.

393
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:13,349
[ Marlene ]
You look great!

394
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:16,557
Honey, l thought you were going
to wear that dress l bought you.

395
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:19,074
ls there something wrong
with what l'm wearing?

396
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:23,034
That's not what l meant.
Um... boy you look good!

397
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:27,153
[ Marlene ] You look beautiful.
Let's go. l'm starving.

398
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:29,071
You have the number
where we'll be.

399
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:31,270
l do. Have fun.

400
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:33,920
Bye.

401
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:40,998
[ Scream ]

402
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:44,829
Zombies.
The living dead.

403
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:48,270
This is great! Mom never
lets me watch these movies.

404
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:51,397
That's why we have
to keep it a secret.

405
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:53,715
Do you know what
a secret is, Emma?

406
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:57,236
Yeah, something
you can't tell anybody...

407
00:32:57,320 --> 00:32:59,993
- No matter what.
- That's right.

408
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:03,999
Now we have our own little
secret club. That's our sign.

409
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:09,875
lt was fun meeting your
Aunt Marlene and Uncle Marty.

410
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:12,560
They've known your mom and dad
a long time, huh?

411
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:14,471
Aunt Marlene grew up
with daddy.

412
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:18,872
They used to be boyfriend
and girlfriend when they were little.

413
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,230
ls that right?

414
00:33:21,360 --> 00:33:24,113
Do you have
any boyfriends?

415
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:28,159
- No, l hate boys.
- You do?

416
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:32,068
lf l tell you something, you
promise not to tell anybody?

417
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:34,549
l promise.
Secret club.

418
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,432
Well...

419
00:33:36,560 --> 00:33:39,791
this mean kid at school,
his name is Roth,

420
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:42,110
he's been really mean
to me.

421
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,834
But he said if l told,
l'd be dead meat.

422
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:47,633
He said that to you?

423
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:50,877
- Did your mother do anything about it?
- She tried...

424
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,468
but she couldn't help.

425
00:33:58,680 --> 00:34:01,069
You never, ever...

426
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,958
let an attractive woman take
a power position in your home.

427
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:06,275
- lt's very bad business.
- A power position.

428
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:09,312
You heard what l said.

429
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,670
What's that saying?

430
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:14,678
- ''The hand with the baby...'' that...
- Hey, Marl?

431
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:17,194
How much did you get for
the Fletcher house last week?

432
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:19,840
Three...
and change.

433
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:22,918
All l'm saying is
you have to watch your back.

434
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:27,033
l'm serious!
There's too much pressure.

435
00:34:27,160 --> 00:34:30,948
A woman can feel like a failure if
she doesn't bring in 50 grand a year...

436
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:35,318
and still make time for
blow jobs and homemade lasagna.

437
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:38,358
Marlene's not
much of a cook.

438
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:42,992
Marlene, l think l'm
gonna bum one of these.

439
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:46,196
You're such
a bad influence.

440
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:49,113
He only smokes
around you now.

441
00:34:49,240 --> 00:34:52,277
- One isn't gonna kill me.
- Oh, l got it.

442
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:54,516
''The hand that rocks
the cradle...

443
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:58,070
is the hand
that rules the world.''

444
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:16,470
You wanna look
at the baby?

445
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:19,160
Ahh, look.

446
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,071
Hi!

447
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:24,237
Ahh, look, honey.

448
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:28,279
- Boy or a girl?
- Boy. His name's Joe.

449
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:32,154
- How old?
- Three months.

450
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:34,430
He is beautiful.

451
00:35:34,560 --> 00:35:37,518
- Thank you.
- He has your eyes, you know.

452
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:42,709
Do you really
think so?

453
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,990
Absolutely!

454
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:49,318
Do you have
any other children?

455
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:52,796
Yes, he has a sister.
Her name's Emma.

456
00:35:52,920 --> 00:35:55,912
She looks more like
her father though.

457
00:35:56,000 --> 00:36:00,198
We have one more too,
don't we, sweetheart?

458
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:10,552
- Peyton.
- Hi, Emma.

459
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:13,877
Tell me, which one
is he? Where?

460
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,951
Take that!

461
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:20,750
- The one with the blue
and grey striped shirt?
- Mm-hmm.

462
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,671
Okay.

463
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:32,394
[ Arguing ]

464
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:39,200
- Watch it, Trippy!
- Sorry, Roth.

465
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,788
Ouch! My arm! My arm!

466
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:45,708
l got a message for you, Roth.
Leave Emma alone.

467
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:48,792
lf you don't, l'm gonna
rip your fucking head off!

468
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,194
Ow!

469
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:52,748
l get it, ma'am.
Let me go!

470
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:55,149
Don't forget it.

471
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:59,592
[ Girl ]
Awesome! Wow, that was cool.

472
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:02,672
Ha-ha ha-ha-ha.

473
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:09,192
Secret club.

474
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:18,234
Good morning.

475
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:26,030
What's the matter?

476
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:28,515
You're not hungry,
sweetheart?

477
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:30,517
Shh-shh-shh.

478
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:32,591
Claire, l thought...

479
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,955
maybe you could use
a cup of coffee.

480
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:37,554
Oh, thanks.

481
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:39,636
- Peyton?
- Yeah?

482
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:42,314
Have you noticed anything
different about Joe?

483
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:45,676
No, l haven't.
Why, is something wrong?

484
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,469
No. l was just wondering.

485
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:52,831
l'm real tired. Michael was up all
night finishing his E.P.A. proposal.

486
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:55,952
- l got up at 4:30 to help him type it.
- l hope it works out.

487
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:57,917
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

488
00:37:58,040 --> 00:37:59,996
- See you tonight.
- You're not gonna have pancakes?

489
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:02,680
Nah, l've got to go to Federal Express
before l go to the lab.

490
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:05,877
Let me. That's the last thing
you need to worry about.

491
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:08,713
You have the time?
My proposal has to go out today.

492
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:11,314
Okay. Thanks.
l love you.

493
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:13,476
