- Bye, Michael.

494
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:27,392
[ Peyton ] How long have you
been volunteering here?

495
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:29,476
Gee, about seven years.

496
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:33,388
These days, l mainly take care
of the morning maintenance.

497
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:37,871
- Hi, Claire.
- Hi, Stan.

498
00:38:37,960 --> 00:38:40,520
Kinda like a big
botanist family here,

499
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:43,871
- right, Stan?
- Yep.

500
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:47,310
We sit around talking
about root rot,

501
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:51,718
drainage properties of shredded bark
and other topics like that.

502
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,917
[ Peyton ] ls your greenhouse gonna be
something like this one?

503
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:03,272
Oh, well, hopefully.
On a much smaller scale.

504
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:06,193
l've always loved
growing anything.

505
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:09,397
When l was little,
my parents thought l was crazy.

506
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:12,159
They thought l should've
been born on a farm.

507
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,756
[ Cooing ]

508
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:19,189
Hey!

509
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:23,393
Ohh!
Hello.

510
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:25,351
Hello!

511
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:31,116
Do you have relatives
in Seattle?

512
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:33,350
Oh no.
No, l don't.

513
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:36,193
My husband
was my only family.

514
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:40,598
He's the only one who ever...
really understood me.

515
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:43,638
He took care of me.

516
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:48,950
He was murdered.

517
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:52,152
Murdered?

518
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:58,069
They never caught
who did it.

519
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,953
But l firmly believe...

520
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:03,469
what goes around,
comes around.

521
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:09,191
ls there a
bathroom here?

522
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:14,115
- Yeah, down through there
on the right side.
- l'll be right back.

523
00:41:49,120 --> 00:41:51,953
Come here,
little one.

524
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:54,833
Do you need
to be changed?

525
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:09,071
[ Wheezing ]

526
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:15,799
[ Wheezing ]

527
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:21,470
Come here.

528
00:42:21,600 --> 00:42:26,196
[ Wheezing ]
Michael's proposal. l can't find it.

529
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:28,953
lt was in your purse.
l saw you put it in there!

530
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:35,470
- Claire, are you all right?
- Asthma. l'll be okay.

531
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:46,115
Asthma.

532
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:57,394
Michael, it...
just disappeared.

533
00:42:57,520 --> 00:43:01,593
l retraced my steps. l spoke to
the manager in the restaurant.

534
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:04,314
He said he'd call
in the morning.

535
00:43:04,440 --> 00:43:06,715
What did they say
when you called again?

536
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:09,195
They said they'd
consider it next quarter.

537
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:12,238
- But they said they'd consider it?
- Claire, come on.

538
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:14,709
We've been over this.

539
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:18,674
Look, everything
is gonna be okay.

540
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:21,752
- Michael, l'm so sorry.
- l know you are, honey.

541
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:23,836
l know you are.

542
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:27,032
Maybe l left it
at the botanicals.

543
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:29,720
l'm going to
get back to work.

544
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:32,757
l'm sorry.

545
00:43:43,640 --> 00:43:45,517
[ Crying ]

546
00:43:53,520 --> 00:43:57,035
- Michael, l'm worried about Joe.
- Why, what's wrong?

547
00:43:57,120 --> 00:44:00,874
Well, it's
his eating habits.

548
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:03,554
He's not nursing
the way he used to.

549
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:05,955
How long has this
been going on?

550
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:09,675
- lt's not all the time,
but... a couple of weeks.
- Did you call the doctor?

551
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:11,716
- Yeah.
- What'd she say?

552
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:15,355
She said it's fine as long
as he keeps gaining weight.

553
00:44:15,480 --> 00:44:18,950
- Well... l'm sure he's fine, honey.
- Okay.

554
00:44:21,920 --> 00:44:23,831
Someone named Peyton
is here to see you.

555
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:26,793
- Peyton's here?
- She's waiting in your office.

556
00:44:29,240 --> 00:44:31,470
