that the foot?

587
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:07,829
No, that's part
of the fur.

588
00:47:09,840 --> 00:47:11,637
Oh!

589
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:13,716
Okay, l see.

590
00:47:13,840 --> 00:47:16,434
That's a piece
of art.

591
00:47:16,520 --> 00:47:18,511
- l knew you'd see it.
- Yeah.

592
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:21,154
Yeah.

593
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:24,238
- Hi, Emma.
- Hi, Peyton.

594
00:47:24,320 --> 00:47:26,356
Hi, Solomon.

595
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:29,233
Emma, why don't you go inside.
l've got to talk to Solomon.

596
00:47:29,320 --> 00:47:31,151
- Okay.
- Okay.

597
00:47:37,680 --> 00:47:39,875
Are you a retard?

598
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:42,036
No.

599
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:49,079
Did you like
looking at me?

600
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:57,709
Did you like...
looking at me?

601
00:48:02,840 --> 00:48:06,515
Don't fuck with me,
retard.

602
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:11,869
My version of the story
will be...

603
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:15,310
better than yours.

604
00:48:21,960 --> 00:48:24,315
l won't let
you hurt them.

605
00:48:24,440 --> 00:48:26,715
They're my friends.

606
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:33,078
l won't let
you hurt them!

607
00:48:36,920 --> 00:48:39,070
Oh boy.

608
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:53,111
Solomon!

609
00:48:55,720 --> 00:48:58,917
Would you step inside
for a minute?

610
00:49:02,160 --> 00:49:04,037
Okay.

611
00:49:15,920 --> 00:49:18,115
Surprise!

612
00:49:19,680 --> 00:49:21,750
lt's for you,
big guy.

613
00:49:25,680 --> 00:49:28,399
l was in charge
of picking it out.

614
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:30,948
Ohh.

615
00:49:31,040 --> 00:49:34,271
You're my friends.

616
00:49:34,400 --> 00:49:36,675
Oh my.

617
00:49:36,800 --> 00:49:39,633
Oh.

618
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:44,271
[ Claire ]
Should've seen his face when we gave
him the bicycle. Emma just adores him.

619
00:49:47,280 --> 00:49:50,477
Claire, there's something
that's been bothering me.

620
00:49:50,560 --> 00:49:53,393
l feel a little awkward
bringing it up.

621
00:49:54,920 --> 00:49:57,559
l've been noticing
some behaviour that...

622
00:49:57,680 --> 00:49:59,910
l feel might be
inappropriate.

623
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:02,673
l'm sorry. What
do you mean, inappropriate?

624
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:08,308
Something about the way
he touches her.

625
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,916
l'm sure you
must've misunderstood.

626
00:50:14,600 --> 00:50:18,798
You're right, Solomon would
never do anything like that.

627
00:50:18,880 --> 00:50:21,792
Besides, it would be obvious
if Emma were keeping a secret.

628
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:28,155
- l'm sorry.
- Oh no, please. lt's okay.

629
00:50:32,880 --> 00:50:35,155
[ Solomon ]
She's coming around.

630
00:50:35,280 --> 00:50:38,989
Whoa! Whoa!

631
00:50:40,480 --> 00:50:42,436
l love you very much,
sweetheart.

632
00:50:42,560 --> 00:50:46,314
You know that
if anything happened,

633
00:50:46,400 --> 00:50:48,391
good or bad,

634
00:50:48,480 --> 00:50:51,233
you can tell me and l
would love you just as much.

635
00:50:51,360 --> 00:50:53,396
Do you know that?

636
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:55,795
Yes.

637
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:58,189
We shouldn't have
any secrets, Emma.

638
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:03,593
Secrets between people who
love each other aren't good.

639
00:51:04,720 --> 00:51:06,597
What's the matter,
baby?

640
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:09,712
Nothing.

641
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:15,716
You don't have to say.

642
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:32,957
Why can't l see
through this glass?

643
00:51:33,080 --> 00:51:35,548
lt's fibreglass,
a different kind of glass.

644
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:39,798
We put real glass in the ceiling
to let the sunlight through.

645
00:51:43,040 --> 00:51:47,192
And this lets the air in so it
doesn't get too hot in the greenhouse.

646
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:51,076
Claire, Joe's intercom
conked out.

647
00:51:51,200 --> 00:51:54,237
l couldn't find any
batteries in the kitchen.

648
00:51:54,360 --> 00:51:58,592
- Do you think Solomon's
got some in his cart?
- Well...

649
00:51:58,720 --> 00:52:02,349
he's got everything else there.
Let me take a look.

650
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:47,073
Do you see
what you've done?

651
00:52:50,200 --> 00:52:52,111
[ Wheezing ]

652
00:53:43,960 --> 00:53:46,076
[ Claire ]
Sweetheart?

653
00:53:46,200 --> 00:53:49,112
Come away from
the window, honey.

654
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:53,910
Emma?

655
00:53:56,000 --> 00:53:57,991
Come sit down.

656
00:54:09,520 --> 00:54:11,397
Peyton.

657
00:54:14,880 --> 00:54:17,348
[ Crying ]

658
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:23,633
But l don't
understand.

659
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:26,314
Why did they take
Solomon away?

660
00:54:26,400 --> 00:54:29,233
l guess your mommy didn't
like Solomon very much.

661
00:54:29,360 --> 00:54:33,876
l wanted to help Solomon, but l was
afraid she'd try to send me away too.

662
00:54:33,960 --> 00:54:37,191
l hate her.

663
00:54:37,280 --> 00:54:40,431
l bet your mommy
wasn't mean like mine.

664
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:44,035
l didn't have
a mommy.

665
00:54:44,160 --> 00:54:47,232
She died when
l was very little.

666
00:54:47,360 --> 00:54:50,193
Your mommy died?

667
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:52,675
Then who took care
of you?

668
00:54:54,880 --> 00:54:57,678
l had to take care
of myself.

669
00:54:57,760 --> 00:55:02,356
Peyton, if something
happens to my mommy,

670
00:55:02,480 --> 00:55:04,835
would you
take care of me?

671
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:07,599
Of course l would.

672
00:55:07,680 --> 00:55:10,035
And your daddy too.

673
00:55:10,160 --> 00:55:12,754
l'd take care
of all of you.

674
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:33,112
- Last of the boxes.
- Yeah.

675
00:55:33,880 --> 00:55:36,633
[ Sigh ]

676
00:55:41,680 --> 00:55:44,717
Emma's gonna be okay,
Claire.

677
00:55:52,480 --> 00:55:56,109
But she's so different
around me lately.

678
00:55:56,240 --> 00:55:59,152
She's not
my little girl.

679
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:02,113
She's so angry...

680
00:56:02,240 --> 00:56:04,435
and guarded.

681
00:56:04,520 --> 00:56:07,796
l think...

682
00:56:07,920 --> 00:56:11,515
