lt's a breast pump.

994
01:28:26,640 --> 01:28:28,949
Breast pump?

995
01:28:30,920 --> 01:28:34,196
She used it to keep
her milk up.

996
01:28:35,520 --> 01:28:37,590
[ Tyres Screeching ]

997
01:28:49,600 --> 01:28:52,478
- l don't understand where
she could be all this time.
- l don't either.

998
01:28:57,840 --> 01:29:00,035
Here she is.

999
01:29:04,840 --> 01:29:07,274
- Honey, where have you been?
- Michael, l've got--

1000
01:29:12,280 --> 01:29:15,272
Hi, Claire, we were
worried about you.

1001
01:29:24,400 --> 01:29:27,836
- Claire, my God!
- She's Dr Mott's widow, Michael.

1002
01:29:27,920 --> 01:29:30,229
She's what?

1003
01:29:30,320 --> 01:29:32,959
Get out
of our house.

1004
01:29:33,080 --> 01:29:36,516
She's turning on me, Michael,
just like you said she would.

1005
01:29:36,640 --> 01:29:40,315
She doesn't realize how l've come
through for this family.

1006
01:29:41,800 --> 01:29:44,234
You have to tell her,
tell her about us.

1007
01:29:44,360 --> 01:29:48,558
There's nothing to tell.
You should leave.

1008
01:29:48,680 --> 01:29:52,116
Michael, what are
you saying?

1009
01:29:52,200 --> 01:29:54,794
You told me there was
only one woman for you.

1010
01:29:54,920 --> 01:29:58,959
l meant Claire,
my wife.

1011
01:30:02,400 --> 01:30:06,757
Okay, fine.

1012
01:30:06,880 --> 01:30:09,440
l'll just get my baby
and we'll be on our way.

1013
01:30:13,240 --> 01:30:17,631
l-- l meant,
l'll just go get my things.

1014
01:30:17,760 --> 01:30:20,354
Michael.

1015
01:30:20,480 --> 01:30:24,075
You don't understand.
l mean, leave now.

1016
01:30:24,200 --> 01:30:26,555
We'll send your things.

1017
01:30:26,640 --> 01:30:28,949
You're right, Michael.
That's best.

1018
01:30:40,000 --> 01:30:41,797
Peyton, the keys.

1019
01:30:43,840 --> 01:30:45,637
Oh, of course.

1020
01:30:48,680 --> 01:30:51,672
l'm sorry.
You've been so kind.

1021
01:30:51,800 --> 01:30:53,756
Mommy, Daddy,
what's happening?

1022
01:30:53,880 --> 01:30:55,677
Emma, stay there!

1023
01:30:55,800 --> 01:30:59,998
[ Peyton ] lt's okay, Emma.
Mommy and Daddy want me to leave.

1024
01:31:00,080 --> 01:31:02,230
Goodbye, Peyton.

1025
01:31:03,800 --> 01:31:05,916
[ Emma ]
Peyton!

1026
01:31:14,280 --> 01:31:16,555
[ Claire ]
Call the police!

1027
01:31:16,680 --> 01:31:18,272
Claire, calm down.

1028
01:31:18,400 --> 01:31:20,914
You don't know
what she's capable of!

1029
01:31:21,000 --> 01:31:22,353
We have her keys!

1030
01:31:22,440 --> 01:31:25,273
l think she rigged
the greenhouse for me!

1031
01:31:25,400 --> 01:31:28,790
All right,
get the kids' things.

1032
01:31:28,920 --> 01:31:31,992
- We'll go to a hotel.
- Go upstairs, sweetheart.

1033
01:31:34,400 --> 01:31:36,470
[ Michael ] Can you get someone
over here right away?

1034
01:31:36,600 --> 01:31:39,114
[ Dispatcher ]
But it's not an emergency situation.

1035
01:31:39,240 --> 01:31:43,791
- Well, no.
- l'll have a car there
as soon as l can.

1036
01:31:43,880 --> 01:31:45,950
All right,
we live at 808 Yakima.

1037
01:31:46,080 --> 01:31:49,834
Emma, sweetheart, we're gonna
go away for a few days, okay?

1038
01:31:49,960 --> 01:31:52,793
You can bring
dolly with you.

1039
01:31:59,400 --> 01:32:03,837
[ From ''Pirates Of Penzance'' ]

1040
01:32:28,800 --> 01:32:31,155
Peyton?

1041
01:32:38,760 --> 01:32:40,955
Peyton?

1042
01:33:11,320 --> 01:33:13,470
[ Alarm ]

1043
01:33:24,040 --> 01:33:25,439
[ Groaning ]

1044
01:33:27,320 --> 01:33:29,959
- Michael?
- Daddy?

1045
01:33:43,680 --> 01:33:46,114
Emma, l want you to lock
this door behind me.

1046
01:33:46,240 --> 01:33:50,392
- Don't open it until l come
back, do you understand?
- Yeah.

1047
01:33:50,520 --> 01:33:53,637
Stay here.

1048
01:34:05,120 --> 01:34:07,839
Michael?

1049
01:34:36,000 --> 01:34:38,719
[ Glass Breaking ]

1050
01:34:47,320 --> 01:34:49,072
- [ Screams ]
- Claire.

1051
01:34:49,160 --> 01:34:51,071
Oh.

1052
01:34:53,200 --> 01:34:57,318
- Michael.
- l'm okay. She's in the house.

1053
01:35:01,480 --> 01:35:04,313
l-- l can't move.

1054
01:35:04,440 --> 01:35:06,510
My legs are broken.

1055
01:35:06,600 --> 01:35:09,433
- l'll get the kids.
- Call the police.

1056
01:35:19,000 --> 01:35:21,036
[ Door Creaking ]

1057
01:35:26,760 --> 01:35:29,274
Mommy?

1058
01:35:45,280 --> 01:35:48,955
- 9-1-1, what is your emergency?
- Hello, yeah.

1059
01:35:49,040 --> 01:35:51,998
We need help at
808 North Yakima.

1060
01:35:52,120 --> 01:35:53,951
Mommy!

1061
01:36:00,920 --> 01:36:03,718
[ Yelling ]
My family!

1062
01:36:10,320 --> 01:36:13,676
lt's my family.

1063
01:36:24,640 --> 01:36:26,551
lt's okay, Emma.

1064
01:36:26,680 --> 01:36:30,070
Mommy's here.

1065
01:36:31,600 --> 01:36:34,876
l'm gonna take you and Joe.
We're gonna have a real family.

1066
01:36:34,960 --> 01:36:37,076
You never have to see
those people again.

1067
01:36:38,760 --> 01:36:41,718
So tell your mommy,
where's Joe?

1068
01:36:41,800 --> 01:36:43,836
Huh?

1069
01:36:43,960 --> 01:36:46,235
Where is he?

1070
01:36:47,480 --> 01:36:49,471
He's in there.

1071
01:36:57,800 --> 01:37:00,792
You're not my mommy!

1072
01:37:05,360 --> 01:37:07,510
Emma!

1073
01:37:08,400 --> 01:37:10,231
[ Crying ]

1074
01:37:10,360 --> 01:37:13,397
[ Crying ]

1075
01:37:16,040 --> 01:37:19,157
[ Crying ]

1076
01:37:19,240 --> 01:37:21,231
[ Pounding ]

1077
01:37:22,760 --> 01:37:25,115
[ Pounding ]

1078
01:37:34,600 --> 01:37:37,034
- [ Crying ]
- Shh, quiet.

1079
01:37:46,760 --> 01:37:48,637
[ Peyton ]
Emma!

1080
01:37:48,720 --> 01:37:51,029
Emma!

1081
01:37:57,800 --> 01:37:59,916
Emma.

1082
01:38:00,040 --> 01:38:02,395
You're being
very bad, Emma.

1083
01:38:02,520 --> 01:38:04,954
[ Crying ]

1084
01:38:08,040 --> 01:38:10,679
[ Crying ]

1085
01:38:13,160 --> 01:38:15,037
[ Crying ]

1086
01:38:20,760 --> 01:38:24,389
[ Crying ]

1087
01:38:32,360 --> 01:38:35,193
[ Crying ]

1088
01:38:46,600 --> 01:38:48,158
- [ Gasp ]
- [ Crying ]

1089
01:38:50,760 --> 01:38:52,796
You.

1090
01:38:52,920 --> 01:38:56,754
[ Crying ]

1091
01:38:56,840 --> 01:38:59,035
- You give him over.
- No!

1092
01:38:59,160 --> 01:39:00,991
- No?
- No!

1093
01:39:01,120 --> 01:39:03,759
You give me my baby or
l'll bash your skull in!

1094
01:39:03,880 --> 01:39:06,394
Peyton!

1095
01:39:09,880 --> 01:39:11,711
lt's my family,
Peyton.

1096
01:39:23,800 --> 01:39:26,917
Don't hurt my mommy!

1097
01:39:29,160 --> 01:39:32,470
[ Wheezing ]

1098
01:39:39,720 --> 01:39:42,518
Something the matter,
Claire?

1099
01:39:42,600 --> 01:39:46,354
[ Wheezing ]

1100
01:39:49,160 --> 01:39:53,438
When your husband makes love to you,
it's my face he sees.

1101
01:39:54,880 --> 01:39:57,155
When your baby's hungry,

1102
01:39:57,280 --> 01:39:59,350
it's my breast
that feeds him.

1103
01:39:59,440 --> 01:40:02,193
Look at you.

1104
01:40:02,280 --> 01:40:04,714
When push
comes to shove,

1105
01:40:04,840 --> 01:40:07,832
you can't even breathe.

1106
01:40:07,920 --> 01:40:10,514
[ Wheezing ]

1107
01:40:17,560 --> 01:40:19,198
- No.
- [ Crying ]

1108
01:40:19,320 --> 01:40:21,595
- Now give him to me.
- No!

1109
01:40:25,000 --> 01:40:27,355
[ Groan ]

1110
01:40:40,360 --> 01:40:43,079
No!

1111
01:40:44,680 --> 01:40:46,671
Owww!

1112
01:40:46,760 --> 01:40:48,591
Noooo!

1113
01:41:13,640 --> 01:41:16,154
[ Cooing ]

1114
01:41:16,280 --> 01:41:18,748
Oh, Solomon.

1115
01:41:18,880 --> 01:41:22,555
He's okay.
l-- l didn't hurt him.

1116
01:41:22,680 --> 01:41:25,353
- l know, l know.
- Okay?

1117
01:41:25,480 --> 01:41:27,436
Shhh.

1118
01:41:27,560 --> 01:41:30,358
[ Solomon ]
Emma! Emma, it's okay.

1119
01:41:30,440 --> 01:41:33,591
Come on, come on,
up we go.

1120
01:41:35,120 --> 01:41:38,192
- Mommy!
- Oh.

1121
01:41:43,960 --> 01:41:46,758
Let's go down
to daddy, okay?

1122
01:41:49,000 --> 01:41:51,992
Solomon, l need you
to do something for me.

1123
01:41:52,120 --> 01:41:53,997
l need you to take
Joey downstairs.

1124
01:41:54,120 --> 01:41:57,317
Oh no, l'm not supposed to...

1125
01:41:57,440 --> 01:41:59,476
handle the baby.

1126
01:41:59,600 --> 01:42:02,398
That's okay.

1127
01:42:02,480 --> 01:42:04,710
l trust you, Solomon.

1128
01:42:11,080 --> 01:42:13,640
lt's okay?

1129
01:42:13,760 --> 01:42:16,513
Okay? Yeah.

1130
01:42:16,640 --> 01:42:20,952
- Oh boy. Oh. There you are.
- [ Siren ]

1131
01:42:21,040 --> 01:42:23,190
- Come on, sweetheart.
- [ Solomon ] Oh, he's a big baby.

1132
01:42:23,280 --> 01:42:28,798
- Let's go and get Daddy.
- Oh, my... little baby.

1133
01:42:28,920 --> 01:42:31,480
Solomon?

1134
01:42:31,600 --> 01:42:34,114
Come on.

1135
01:42:34,200 --> 01:42:36,509
- [ Siren ]
- Oh boy.

